The paper proposes a multi-view learning algorithm based on constrained clustering, which is a common topic in machine learning and falls under the category of "cs.LG" (Machine Learning). The algorithm also involves propagating constraints and using a local similarity measure, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence ("cs.AI"). The paper also mentions the use of clustering models, which is a common topic in natural language processing ("cs.CL"). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of multi-view learning in computer vision ("cs.CV") and the evaluation of clustering performance ("cs.SI", Social and Information Networks).
